<h2>Key points</h2><ul><li>The 3P approach to pain management is a mix of psychological, physical and pharmacological methods to treat and manage pain.</li><li>Physical approaches involve encouraging your teen to use pacing to help them choose the right level of physical activity and balance activity with periods of rest.</li><li>Psychological approaches include techniques such as distraction, guided imagery and relaxation and, if needed, therapy to address unwanted thoughts and behaviours related to pain.</li><li>Pharmacological approaches include over-the-counter and prescription pain relievers.</li></ul>
</div>
