<p>
<a href="/healthaz/pain/anaesthesia/chronic-pain/">Chronic pain</a> treatments involve a mix of psychological, physical and pharmacological (medication) strategies. Together, these are termed the 3Ps of pain control. Like three legs of a stool, the 3Ps are complementary, or supportive, to one another.</p>
<figure class="asset-c-80">
<span class="asset-image-title">3P approach for managing pain in teens</span>
<picture><source sizes="356px" srcset="/globalassets/assets/chronicpain_3ps_teens.png?format=webp&amp;width=356&amp;quality=60 356w" type="image/webp"/><source sizes="356px" srcset="/globalassets/assets/chronicpain_3ps_teens.png?width=356&amp;quality=60 356w"/><img alt="Three overlapping circles containing psychological, physical and pharmacological strategies" decoding="async" loading="lazy" src="/globalassets/assets/chronicpain_3ps_teens.png?width=356&amp;quality=60" width="356"/></picture>
<figcaption>The 3P approach combines psychological, physical and pharmacological strategies to manage pain. Each strategy is described below.</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>No single strategy will likely be the answer, so it is important to be open to a variety of options if your teen has chronic pain.</p> </div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div aria-controls="article-Procedure" aria-expanded="false" class="panel-heading clickable rs_preserve" role="button" tabindex="0">
<span class="panel-heading-collapsable">Treatment</span>
